    "plan_content": "The plan is complete. Here's a summary of what I've designed:\n\n---\n\n## PulseBoard Channel Plugin — Implementation Plan\n\n**14 new files** all under `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files touched.\n\n### Key design decisions based on codebase analysis:\n\n| Aspect | Decision | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|\n| Account model | Single-account (`createTopLevelChannelConfigAdapter`) | Mirrors Nostr; PulseBoard = one token per server |\n| Chat types | `[\"direct\", \"group\"]` | Groups = named boards (`#general`), direct = `@username` |\n| Text chunk limit | `4000` chars | As specified; matches Nostr's limit |\n| DM default policy | `\"pairing\"` | Secure default; same as Nostr |\n| Delivery mode | `\"direct\"` | Gateway holds active `PulseBoardClient` per account |\n| Runtime store | `createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>` | IRC/Nostr pattern |\n| `runtime-api.ts` | Re-exports from generic SDK subpaths | No `openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard` exists yet |\n\n### File roles:\n- **`package.json`** + **`openclaw.plugin.json`** — metadata, id alignment (`pulseboard` everywhere), config schema\n- **`src/config-schema.ts`** — Zod schemas for `serverUrl`, `token`, `dmPolicy`, `allowFrom`\n- **`src/types.ts`** — `ResolvedPulseBoardAccount`, `CoreConfig`, account resolution functions\n- **`src/runtime.ts`** — `createPluginRuntimeStore` → `get/setPulseBoardRuntime`\n- **`src/client.ts`** — Fictional `PulseBoardClient` with stubbed `connect/disconnect/sendDirect/sendBoard`\n- **`src/send.ts`** — `sendMessagePulseBoard()` routing `#board` vs `@user` targets\n- **`src/setup-surface.ts`** — Setup wizard (collects `serverUrl` + `token`)\n- **`runtime-api.ts`** — Thin barrel re-exporting from generic SDK subpaths (`direct-dm`, `channel-pairing`, `status-helpers`, etc.)\n- **`src/channel.ts`** — `createChatChannelPlugin()` with full lifecycle: gateway `startAccount`, pairing, DM security, outbound send\n- **`src/channel.test.ts`** — 8+ unit tests covering metadata, capabilities, chunk limit, target normalization, DM policy\n- **`index.ts`** / **`setup-entry.ts`** / **`api.ts`** — Standard entry points",
